    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Social Security, as Seen at 19 and 65</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gerald M Taylor letter warns of effect of huge sums of Social Security money hitting stock market if it is to be privately invested</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I have noticed that one thing is missing from the discussion about investing Social Security funds in the stock market (front page, May 16). It is the effect of all of that money hitting the market, and the effect of withdrawals when the investors reach retirement age.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I have noticed that one thing is missing from the discussion about investing Social Security funds in the stock market (front page, May 16). It is the effect of all of that money hitting the market, and the effect of withdrawals when the investors reach retirement age.</p>
        <p>It would be a major service if some qualified people began to discuss the missing factor.</p>
        <p>GERALD M. TAYLOR  Tampa, Fla., May 18, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
